  <bioghist id="aspace_a9acfa97afd8e0ddc0e55d85a256f05d">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Janet "Ginger" Pinkard was involved in radical activities, mostly in New York City, in the 1930s and 1940s. While attending demonstrations, concerts and films, she collected programs, song-sheets and songbooks relating specifically to those events and to radical politics in general.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_e40af6d6c177f81df74609212410829c">
